VARIABLES IN ANSIBLE ACCORDING TO PRIORITY -

1. COMMAND LINE -
ansible-playbook playbook_name.yaml -e ansible_ssh_user=root  //variable (Highest Priority)

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

2. INSIDE HOSTS/INVENTORY FILE -
   //(Medium Priority)
EX-

[web]
172.31.46.23 ansible_ssh_user=root ansible_ssh_pass=redhat ansible_ssh_port=22

[app]
172.31.25.137

[app:vars]
ansible_ssh_user=root 
ansible_ssh_pass=redhat 
ansible_ssh_port=22

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

3. INSIDE PLAYBOOK WRITTEN/IMPORTED -
   //(Least Priority)

 EX-

--> Written <--

vars:
  mydir: /tmp/ritesh
  myfile: /etc/passwd
  mypkg:
    - apache2
    - nginx
    - tree

tasks:
 - name: "This task is used to create a directory {{ mydir }}"
   file:
     path: "{{ mydir }}"
     state: directory

--> Imported <--

---
- name: This is a demo playbook
  hosts: all
  become: yes
  vars_files:
    - /myfolder/variables.yaml

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

  


